.TH DISKDIAG 8 "2026" "diskdiag" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
diskdiag \- sequential read latency test with ASCII heatmap
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B diskdiag
.I device
.RI [ block_size_MiB ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B diskdiag
performs a full sequential read of a block device, measures the
latency of each block and renders an ASCII heatmap of results.
Unlike SMART attribute readers, it exercises the actual read path
and reports real-world latency distribution, making it useful for
detecting degraded areas, aging HDD heads or failing flash cells.
.PP
The tool opens the device with
.B O_DIRECT
to bypass the page cache, so results reflect physical media
performance rather than RAM speed.
.PP
If the device or any of its partitions is currently mounted,
.B diskdiag
warns the user and asks for confirmation before proceeding.
Reads are safe (read-only), but latency results may be skewed by
concurrent OS I/O on a live system.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I device
Block device to test, e.g.
.BR /dev/sdb .
Must be readable by the current user (typically requires root).
.TP
.I block_size_MiB
Size of each read block in mebibytes. Defaults to
.BR 1 .
Larger blocks improve throughput measurement; smaller blocks give
finer spatial resolution in the heatmap.
.SH OUTPUT
.TP
.B Progress bar
Shows completion percentage and current block latency in ms.
.TP
.B ASCII heatmap
Each cell represents the average latency of a disk region.
Colour and character encode latency:
.RS
.TP
.B '.'  (green)
< 5 ms \(em fast
.TP
.B 'o'  (green)
< 10 ms
.TP
.B '*'  (green)
< 20 ms \(em normal for HDD
.TP
.B '#'  (yellow)
< 50 ms \(em slow
.TP
.B 'X'  (red)
< 150 ms \(em very slow, investigate
.TP
.B '!'  (magenta)
\(>= 150 ms \(em critical
.TP
.B 'E'  (magenta)
read error (I/O error returned by kernel)
.RE
.TP
.B Statistics
Minimum, average, median, P90, P99 and maximum latency;
throughput in MiB/s; count of slow and error blocks.
.TP
.B Health rating
.RS
.TP
.B HEALTHY
< 1 % slow blocks, no errors
.TP
.B GOOD
1\(en5 % slow blocks
.TP
.B FAIR
> 5 % slow blocks
.TP
.B POOR
read errors or latency \(>= 150 ms detected
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
Test a secondary drive with default 1 MiB blocks:
.PP
.RS
.B sudo diskdiag /dev/sdb
.RE
.PP
Test with 4 MiB blocks for faster throughput measurement:
.PP
.RS
.B sudo diskdiag /dev/sdb 4
.RE
.PP
Stop early at any time with
.BR Ctrl\-C ;
partial results and heatmap are displayed immediately.
.SH NOTES
Always run as root or with read permission on the raw device.
.PP
For the most accurate results, unmount the device before testing
or boot from a live USB when testing the system disk.
.PP
NVMe drives typically show < 1 ms latency; HDDs 5\(en20 ms.
Sustained latency above 50 ms on an HDD suggests head issues or
imminent failure.
.SH BUILD
.nf
gcc -O2 -Wall -o diskdiag diskdiag.c -lm
.fi
.SH AUTHOR
Written as an open diagnostic utility. No warranty expressed or implied.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR smartctl (8),
.BR hdparm (8),
.BR badblocks (8),
.BR nvme (1)
